id: pm-hxp2
title: Extract bundled import/export customizations into installable pm packages
description: "Move Beads and Todo import/export customizations into first-party package roots that can be installed with pm install, keeping the bare CLI focused on storage, item lifecycle, package loading, and extension primitives."
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[5]: beads,extensions,packages,pm-cli,todos
created_at: "2026-05-11T20:21:17.893Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-11T22:20:40.141Z"
author: codex-agent
acceptance_criteria: Beads and Todo packages have package.json pm manifests; pm install works from their package roots in a sandbox project; legacy commands remain available after installation; package docs/tests cover migration and do not require these customizations in bare core.
parent: pm-59gj
resolution: Extracted Beads/Todos into installable first-party packages and fixed the linked-test runtime seeding race found during verification.
expected_result: "Beads/Todos package roots install cleanly, legacy commands remain available after package install, docs/tests cover package-first usage, and full verification stays green."
actual_result: "Package install/import/export E2E passed in an isolated temp project; focused linked pm test, full coverage, quality gates, compatibility, pack dry-run, and npx smoke passed."
comments[8]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-11T20:21:17.893Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: ran pm search beads todos packages installable first-party extension extraction --limit 10 and found only closed historical beads/todos extension work plus existing package-first feature pm-59gj; no open child covers extraction into installable first-party packages."
  "2026-05-11T20:29:54.325Z",codex-agent,"Implementation update: added first-party package roots packages/pm-beads and packages/pm-todos with package.json pm.extensions manifests; pm install beads/todos aliases now resolve through package roots before legacy extension paths; extension entrypoints can load runtimes from package roots or installed local extension copies."
  "2026-05-11T20:32:37.450Z",codex-agent,"Focused verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/package-manifest.spec.ts tests/unit/extension-command.spec.ts tests/unit/builtin-extension-entrypoints.spec.ts tests/unit/beads-command.spec.ts tests/unit/todos-extension.spec.ts tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts (122 tests)."
  "2026-05-11T20:33:31.053Z",codex-agent,"Linked pm test orchestration note: first pm test --run attempt exited before execution with ENOENT on telemetry flush.lock; the linked command itself had already passed directly. Retrying pm test --run with PM_TELEMETRY_DISABLED=1 PM_SENTRY_DISABLED=1 for runner stability, with live telemetry checked separately."
  "2026-05-11T20:36:25.108Z",codex-agent,"Manual temp-project E2E passed: isolated PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH; node dist/cli.js init --defaults; pm install packages/pm-beads and packages/pm-todos; beads import imported 1 item; todos export exported 1 item; package doctor ok; contracts exposed beads import and todos export as installed commands; health and validate both ok in the temp project."
  "2026-05-11T20:42:27.679Z",codex-agent,"Coverage remediation: added package-manifest branch tests for null pm manifests, unknown resource keys, root-level extension package sources, and mixed directory entries after full coverage identified uncovered manifest helper branches."
  "2026-05-11T21:00:48.624Z",codex-agent,"Full coverage restored after manifest branch coverage additions: node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed with 90 files / 1279 tests and 100% statements, branches, functions, and lines."
  "2026-05-11T21:16:54.575Z",codex-agent,"Final evidence: focused linked pm test passed without telemetry disabled (123 tests); node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed with 90 files / 1280 tests and 100% coverage; pnpm typecheck, docs-skills, static, security, version, compatibility, npm pack dry-run, smoke:npx, and isolated package install/import/export E2E all passed. Sentry PM-CLI-P root cause fixed by skipping transient runtime data in linked-test tracker sandboxes."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-11T20:32:39.426Z",codex-agent,"Package aliases that resolve to package roots must still support activate/deactivate by deriving the installed extension manifest name from package.json pm.extensions, not by assuming the alias path itself contains manifest.json."
